WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 382
Chapter 382
(House Bill 1598)
AN ACT concerning
Horse Racing – Racetrack Facility Renewal Account Grants – Alterations
FOR the purpose of authorizing, rather than requiring, a certain racing licensee to receive
a grant for a capital construction plan from the Racetrack Facility Renewal Account
without providing and expending a matching fund; requiring the racing licensee that
receives the grant without providing and expending a matching fund to conduct live
racing in the State for a certain number of years; requiring the State Racing
Commission to recapture certain grant funds under certain circumstances and in a
certain manner; altering the amount of the balance in the Racetrack Facility
Renewal Account that is required to be made available to certain racing licensees if
certain racetracks are closed and no longer used for live racing; and generally
relating to grants from the Racetrack Facility Renewal Account.
BY renumbering
